STEP 1: Setup & SparkSession (Beginner)

Install PySpark: pip install pyspark

STEP 2: Create SparkSession

SparkSession is the entry point of PySpark.

from pyspark.sql import SparkSession

spark = SparkSession.builder \
    .appName("PySpark Basics") \
    .getOrCreate()

print("Spark Version:", spark.version)


Explanation:

SparkSession.builder → builds Spark app

.appName() → name of your application

.getOrCreate() → creates new session or uses existing one
